{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":809,"text":"I once had this nightmare:"},{"time":3007,"text":"I'm standing in the middle\nof a deserted field full of land mines."},{"time":7571,"text":"In real life, I love to hike,"},{"time":10060,"text":"but every time I want to go on a hike,\nit makes me nervous."},{"time":14327,"text":"I have this thought in the back of my mind"},{"time":16875,"text":"that I might lose a limb."}]},{"cues":[{"time":19402,"text":"This underlying fear started 10 years ago,"},{"time":22125,"text":"after I met Mohammed,\na cluster bomb survivor"},{"time":25447,"text":"of the summer 2006\nIsrael-Hezbollah War in Lebanon."},{"time":30303,"text":"Mohammed, like so many\nother survivors all around the world,"},{"time":33581,"text":"had to live through the horrifying\nrepercussions of cluster munitions"},{"time":38592,"text":"on a daily basis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":41122,"text":"When the one-month conflict\nstarted in Lebanon,"},{"time":43785,"text":"I was still working\nat Agence France-Presse in Paris."},{"time":47837,"text":"I remember how I was glued to the screens,"},{"time":50463,"text":"anxiously following the news."},{"time":53155,"text":"I wanted to reassure myself"},{"time":54862,"text":"that the falling bombs\nmissed my parents' home."},{"time":58773,"text":"When I arrived in Beirut\non assignment to cover that war,"},{"time":62335,"text":"I was relieved to be united\nwith my family,"},{"time":64827,"text":"after they had finally managed\nto escape southern Lebanon."},{"time":68744,"text":"The day the war was over,"},{"time":70567,"text":"I remember seeing this image --"},{"time":72742,"text":"one of blocked roads,"},{"time":74209,"text":"of displaced people eagerly rushing\nsouth, back to their homes,"},{"time":78362,"text":"regardless of what they would find."}]},{"cues":[{"time":81374,"text":"An estimated four million\ncluster submunitions"},{"time":84468,"text":"were spread in Lebanon during\nthe 34-day conflict."},{"time":90462,"text":"Mohammed lost both legs\nduring the last week of the conflict."},{"time":94826,"text":"The fact that he lives a five-minute\ndrive from my parents' home"},{"time":97901,"text":"made it easier to follow\nhim through the years."},{"time":100680,"text":"It was now almost 10 years\nsince we first met."},{"time":104309,"text":"I saw the young boy"},{"time":105884,"text":"who had to endure\nphysical and emotional trauma."},{"time":110277,"text":"I saw the teenager who tried\nto offer his friends tattoos,"},{"time":113633,"text":"in return for a set fee of five dollars."},{"time":117170,"text":"And I know the young, jobless man\nwho spends hours surfing the Internet"},{"time":121337,"text":"trying to meet a girl who might\nbecome his girlfriend."},{"time":125408,"text":"His fate and the effects\nof losing his legs"},{"time":128946,"text":"are now his daily reality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":131578,"text":"Survivors of bomb trauma like Mohammed"},{"time":133991,"text":"have to deal with so many details\nthat never occur to us."},{"time":137817,"text":"Who would have imagined"},{"time":139017,"text":"that so many daily tasks we do\nor take for granted,"},{"time":141776,"text":"such as going to the beach or even\npicking up something from the floor,"},{"time":146053,"text":"would become sources\nof stress and anxiety?"},{"time":149886,"text":"Well, that's what eventually\nbecame of Mohammed,"},{"time":152221,"text":"due to his inflexible prosthetic legs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":156465,"text":"Ten years ago, I had no clue\nwhat a cluster bomb was,"},{"time":160159,"text":"nor its horrifying implications."},{"time":162835,"text":"I learned that this indiscriminate\nweapon was used"},{"time":165296,"text":"in so many parts of the world"},{"time":166835,"text":"and continues to kill on a regular basis,"},{"time":169131,"text":"without distinguishing\nbetween a military target"},{"time":172194,"text":"or a child."},{"time":174141,"text":"I naively asked myself,"},{"time":176006,"text":"\"But seriously, who made those weapons?"},{"time":179847,"text":"And what for?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":181687,"text":"Let me explain to you\nwhat a cluster bomb is."},{"time":184179,"text":"It's a large canister\nfilled with bomblets."},{"time":187377,"text":"When it's dropped from the air,"},{"time":189064,"text":"it opens up in midair to release\nhundreds of bomblets."},{"time":193632,"text":"They scatter around wide areas"},{"time":195774,"text":"and on impact,"},{"time":196951,"text":"many fail to explode."},{"time":199348,"text":"Those unexploded ones end up\njust like landmines --"},{"time":202593,"text":"sitting on the ground,"},{"time":203850,"text":"waiting for their next target."},{"time":206560,"text":"If someone steps on them by accident"},{"time":209038,"text":"or picks them up,"},{"time":210220,"text":"they can explode."},{"time":212283,"text":"These weapons are extremely unpredictable,"},{"time":215190,"text":"which makes the threat even bigger."},{"time":217243,"text":"One day, a farmer can work\nhis land without a problem."},{"time":220366,"text":"The next day, he can make fire\nand burn some branches,"},{"time":224345,"text":"and the submunitions close by\ncould be set off because of the heat."},{"time":228762,"text":"The problem is children mistake\nthose bomblets for toys,"},{"time":232335,"text":"because they can look like\nbouncy balls or soda cans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":236943,"text":"Being a documentary photographer,"},{"time":238833,"text":"I decided to go back to Lebanon\na few months after the conflict ended"},{"time":242996,"text":"to meet cluster bomb survivors."},{"time":244993,"text":"And I met a few --"},{"time":246168,"text":"Hussein and Rasha,"},{"time":247765,"text":"who both lost a leg to submunitions."},{"time":250143,"text":"Their stories are similar to so many\nother kids' stories across the world"},{"time":254383,"text":"and are a testimony\nto the horrifying implications"},{"time":257456,"text":"of the continuous use of such weapons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":261332,"text":"That's when I met Mohammed,\nin January 2007."},{"time":265427,"text":"He was 11 years old,"},{"time":266731,"text":"and I met him exactly four months\nafter his accident."},{"time":270777,"text":"When I first saw him,"},{"time":271952,"text":"he was going through painful physiotherapy"},{"time":274095,"text":"to recover from his fresh wounds."},{"time":276547,"text":"Still in shock at such a young age,"},{"time":278843,"text":"Mohammed was struggling\nto get used to his new body."},{"time":282650,"text":"He would even wake up sometimes\nat night wanting to scratch his lost feet."},{"time":288187,"text":"What drew me closer to his story\nwas my instant realization"},{"time":291900,"text":"of the difficulties Mohammed\nwas likely to face in the future --"},{"time":295997,"text":"that what he has been suffering\nwhile adjusting to his injury"},{"time":299346,"text":"at the age of 11,"},{"time":301040,"text":"would increase manyfold."}]},{"cues":[{"time":303771,"text":"Even before his disability,"},{"time":305385,"text":"Mohammed's life wasn't easy."},{"time":307626,"text":"He was born in the Rashidieh Camp\nfor Palestinian refugees,"},{"time":310930,"text":"and this is where he still lives."},{"time":313103,"text":"Lebanon holds some 400,000\nPalestinian refugees,"},{"time":316849,"text":"and they suffer from discriminatory laws."},{"time":319662,"text":"They're not allowed to work\nin the public sector"},{"time":322259,"text":"or practice certain professions"},{"time":324266,"text":"and are denied the right to own property."},{"time":327278,"text":"This is one of the reasons"},{"time":328557,"text":"why Mohammed doesn't really\nregret dropping out of school"},{"time":331324,"text":"right after his injury."},{"time":333397,"text":"He said, \"What's the point\nof a university degree"},{"time":336960,"text":"when I can't find a job to start with?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":341046,"text":"Cluster bomb use creates a vicious circle\nof impact on communities,"},{"time":345284,"text":"and not only the lives of their victims."},{"time":347993,"text":"Many who get injured by this weapon\ndrop out of school,"},{"time":351832,"text":"can't find jobs or even lose their jobs,"},{"time":354293,"text":"therefore losing the ability\nto provide for their families."},{"time":357887,"text":"This is not to mention\nthe continuous physical pain"},{"time":361238,"text":"and the experience of feeling isolated."},{"time":365512,"text":"These weapons affect\nthe poorest of the poor."},{"time":368624,"text":"The high medical cost\nis a burden to the families."},{"time":371884,"text":"They end up relying\non humanitarian agencies,"},{"time":374955,"text":"which is insufficient and unsustainable,"},{"time":377508,"text":"especially when injuries require\nlifelong support to the injured."},{"time":381704,"text":"Ten years after Mohammed's injury,"},{"time":383566,"text":"he is still unable to afford\nproper prosthetic legs."},{"time":387856,"text":"He's very cautious with his steps,"},{"time":389685,"text":"as a couple of falls over the years"},{"time":391727,"text":"brought him embarrassment\namong his friends."},{"time":395218,"text":"He joked that since he doesn't have legs,"},{"time":397321,"text":"some days he tries to walk on his hands."}]},{"cues":[{"time":401054,"text":"One of the worst yet invisible\nimpacts of the weapon"},{"time":404436,"text":"is the psychological scars it leaves."},{"time":407348,"text":"In one of Mohammed's\nearly medical reports,"},{"time":409688,"text":"he was diagnosed with signs of PTSD."},{"time":412755,"text":"He suffered from anxiety,\npoor appetite, sleep disturbance"},{"time":418011,"text":"and showed signs of anger."},{"time":421197,"text":"The reality is Mohammed never received\nproper help to fully recover."},{"time":426271,"text":"His current obsession\nis to leave Lebanon at any cost --"},{"time":430511,"text":"even if it meant embarking\non a hazardous journey"},{"time":433400,"text":"along with refugees drifting towards\nEurope today through the Mediterranean."},{"time":439034,"text":"Knowing how risky such a journey would be,"},{"time":441319,"text":"he said, \"If I were to die on the way,"},{"time":444463,"text":"it doesn't matter.\""},{"time":445747,"text":"To Mohammed, he is dead here, anyway."}]},{"cues":[{"time":450294,"text":"Cluster bombs are a world problem,"},{"time":453326,"text":"as this munition keeps destroying\nand hurting whole communities"},{"time":458011,"text":"for generations to come."},{"time":460618,"text":"In an online interview with the director\nof the Mines Advisory Group,"},{"time":464156,"text":"Jamie Franklin,"},{"time":465331,"text":"he said,"},{"time":466511,"text":"\"The US forces dropped over two million\ntons of munitions over Laos."},{"time":471570,"text":"If they couldn't find\ntheir targets in Vietnam,"},{"time":474279,"text":"there were free-drop areas in Laos\nwhere planes would drop their loads"},{"time":478600,"text":"before going back to base,"},{"time":480619,"text":"because it's dangerous to land\nwith loaded planes.\""},{"time":484653,"text":"According to the International\nCommittee of the Red Cross,"},{"time":487439,"text":"in Laos alone -- one of the poorest\ncountries in the world --"},{"time":490819,"text":"nine to 27 million unexploded\nsubmunitions remain."},{"time":496238,"text":"Some 11,000 people have been killed\nor injured since 1973."},{"time":502691,"text":"This lethal weapon has been used\nby over 20 states during armed conflicts"},{"time":507603,"text":"in over 35 countries,"},{"time":509785,"text":"such as Ukraine, Iraq and Sudan."}]},{"cues":[{"time":514403,"text":"So far, 119 states have joined\nan international treaty"},{"time":518713,"text":"banning cluster bombs,"},{"time":520448,"text":"which is officially called\nthe Convention on Cluster Munitions."},{"time":524417,"text":"But some of the biggest producers\nof cluster munitions --"},{"time":527891,"text":"namely, the United States,\nRussia and China --"},{"time":531254,"text":"remain outside of this lifesaving treaty"},{"time":533748,"text":"and continue to produce them,"},{"time":535709,"text":"reserve the right to produce\nthem in the future,"},{"time":538552,"text":"keep those harmful weapons\nin their stockpiles"},{"time":541302,"text":"and even possibly use them in the future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":545520,"text":"Cluster bombs have reportedly\nbeen used most recently"},{"time":549736,"text":"in the ongoing conflicts\nin Yemen and Syria."},{"time":554122,"text":"According to research\non the worldwide investments"},{"time":556909,"text":"in cluster munitions producers"},{"time":558559,"text":"by Pax, a Dutch-based NGO,"},{"time":561380,"text":"financial institutions invested\nbillions of US dollars"},{"time":565280,"text":"into companies that make\ncluster munitions."},{"time":568660,"text":"The majority of these institutions\nare based in countries"},{"time":572532,"text":"that have not yet signed\nthe Convention on Cluster Munitions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":577114,"text":"Getting back to Mohammed,"},{"time":579165,"text":"one of the few jobs he was able\nto find was picking lemons."},{"time":583505,"text":"When I ask him if it's safe\nto work in the field he said,"},{"time":587091,"text":"\"I'm not sure.\""},{"time":589021,"text":"Research shows that cluster munitions\noften contaminate areas"},{"time":593715,"text":"where agriculture is the main\nsource of income."},{"time":598014,"text":"According to Handicap\nInternational's research,"},{"time":600914,"text":"98 percent of those killed or injured\nby cluster munitions are civilians."},{"time":607479,"text":"Eighty-four percent\nof casualties are males."},{"time":611074,"text":"In countries where\nthese people have no choice"},{"time":613831,"text":"but to work in those fields,"},{"time":615911,"text":"they simply do it"},{"time":617591,"text":"and risk it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":619914,"text":"Mohammed is the only male\nto three sisters."},{"time":623006,"text":"Culturally, he's expected\nto provide for his family,"},{"time":626356,"text":"but he simply can't."},{"time":628117,"text":"He tried to have so many different jobs,"},{"time":630225,"text":"but he couldn't keep any\ndue to his physical disability"},{"time":633815,"text":"and the less-than-friendly environment\nto people with disabilities,"},{"time":637304,"text":"to say the least."},{"time":639583,"text":"It hurts him a lot when he goes\nout looking for a job,"},{"time":642935,"text":"and he's turned away"},{"time":644152,"text":"with a small amount of money\npaid to him out of pity."},{"time":647650,"text":"He said, \"I'm not here to beg for money,"},{"time":650405,"text":"I just want to earn it.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":653764,"text":"Mohammed today is 21 years old."},{"time":656206,"text":"He's illiterate,"},{"time":657428,"text":"and he communicates with voice messages."},{"time":660521,"text":"Here is one of his messages."}]},{"cues":[{"time":663234,"text":"(Audio) Mohammed: (Speaking in Arabic)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":671325,"text":"Laura Boushnak:\nHe said, \"My dream is to run,"},{"time":673924,"text":"and I'm pretty sure once I start running,"},{"time":676125,"text":"I would never stop.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":677659,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":678866,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}